The article discusses Executive Order 13509, which was issued by President Barack Obama on June 23, 2009. The order establishes the White House Council on Automotive Communities and Workers, with the aim of addressing the decline in employment in the auto industry and the negative impact on automotive communities. The Council consists of various members from different government departments and agencies. Its functions include coordinating policies and programs, advising the President on legislation and policy proposals, providing recommendations for changes to federal policies and programs, and ensuring a coordinated federal response to the needs of affected states and communities. The Council is also responsible for conducting outreach to various stakeholders to gather concerns, ideas, and policy options for revitalizing automotive communities. The order specifies that the Council will terminate after two years unless extended by the President.